SIMPLE: imprecate
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Imprecate
<hw>Im"pre*cate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Imprecated</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Imprecating</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L.
<ets>imprecatus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>imprecari</ets> to imprecate; pref.
<ets>im-</ets> in, on + <ets>precari</ets> to pray. See
<er>Pray</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To call down by prayer, as
something hurtful or calamitous.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Imprecate</qex> the vengeance of Heaven on the guilty
empire.</q> <rj><qau>Mickle.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To invoke evil upon; to curse; to swear
at.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>In vain we blast the ministers of Fate,⟦br⟧
And the forlorn physicians <qex>imprecate</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Rochester.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Imprecation</ent>⟦br⟧
